		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=MichaelSBlack&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>I decided to try the bard life and it appears fun, except one thing...I give my bard an instrament (he is lvl 18) and give him at least one point in his skill of that instrament, and key in a song for him to play that matches the instrament and he gits exp in singing!&nbsp;&nbsp;What more do I have to do to get him strength in his instrament skill?  This is an interesting class that appears to be fun to play.  I have a lot to learn, I have no idea how to make the instraments work.  =)  Thanks for the time and information from an experianced bard.</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td><td align="right" id="fs8" >3 Replies</td></tr></table>
