		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=camenae&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>I had some trouble with this too... after about lvl 15 you have to have an instrument and the skill points in that instrument to make the songs work. <br><br>What you do is, get one of your lower-level songs (Disruptive Discord works well for brass) and play it over and over to build up skill. I went to Shadeweaver's, loaded my brass instrument, and just played the song at all the bugs and hoppers and things that were green - they died instantly and I built up my skill. Then load up your instrument and try one of the higher-level songs; eventually it will work. <br><br>Another tip: Use the bandolier to switch quickly between instruments so that you can still twist many different songs.</p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />Aafimek and Camenae running for the zone line - hoping they can make it out to fight another day - pulled a mob and lost the group and finally there's the PoK Book! - Odelally odelally golly what a day!</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8">Posting from Erollisi Marr</td></tr></table>
